recipieName: Fried egg on toast with apple, yogurt & latte
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Eggs, 1 large (1.8oz)
  • Whole-grain bread, 1 slice(s), toasted (1.1oz)
  • Sriracha, 1 tsp(s), optional (0.2oz)
  • Apple, 1 small (5.3oz)
  • Non-fat plain Greek yogurt, ⅓ cup(s) (2.6oz)
  • Latte, plain, nonfat milk, 1 small takeaway cup(s) (11.5oz)
recipeInstructions:
Heat the oil in a non-stick pan over medium heat. Once the oil is hot, crack the egg into the pan. Cook for 3 minutes, or until cooked to your liking.

Remove the egg from the pan and place on top of warm toasted bread. Drizzle over sriracha, if using.

Enjoy with a sliced apple dipped in yogurt.

Follow with a skim latte.

recipieName: Cumin spiced egg sandwich
recipeIngredients:
• Eggs, 1 large, raw (1.8oz)
  • Light mayo, 1 tbsp(s) (0.5oz)
  • Red onion, chopped, 1½ tbsp(s) (0.5oz)
  • Cumin, ground, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es), ground
  • Lemon, ¼ medium, juiced (0.7oz)
  • Whole-wheat bread, 2 slice(s) (2.3oz)
  • Carrot, shredded, 4 tbsp(s) (1oz)
  • Cherry tomatoes, 5 cherry tomato(es), diced (3oz)
  • Baby spinach, 1 handful(s) (0.8oz)
recipeInstructions:
Place egg in a small saucepan, covering with cold water and bringing to the boil over high heat. Once boiling, immediately reduce heat to medium and gently boil for 8 minutes. Remove from hot water and place in ice cold water until cool.

Remove egg from water, discard shell and mash egg together with mayo, onion, cumin, black pepper, and lemon juice.

Spread 1 slice of bread with curried egg mixture and top with carrot, tomatoes and spinach. Top with other slice to make a sandwich.

TIP: For cooler days, toast sandwich in a sandwich press for a warm lunch option. If preferred, add salad vegetables after toasting.

Cook eggs at the start of the week and store in the fridge for use in lunch meals and snacks. Boiled eggs can be kept for up to one week in the fridge, with their shells left on.
NutritionInfo: Calories324Total Fat11.5 g- Saturated Fat2.7 gCholesterol188 mgSodium525 mgTotal Carbohydrate39.7 g- Dietary Fiber7.3 g- Total Sugars8.4 g-- Added Sugars0 gProtein16.8 g

recipieName: Leftover Lentil ratatouille roasted mushrooms
recipeInstructions:
Reheat leftover portion of Lentil ratatouille roasted mushrooms prepared earlier in the week.

Spoon ½ teaspoon oil over arugula and scatter over reheated portion of lentil ratatouille and roasted mushrooms. Season to taste. Serve.

recipieName: Hummus bliss bowl
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 4 tsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Baby carrot, 8 medium, scrubbed and cut lengthways (2.8oz)
  • Red bell pepper, raw, 1 medium, cut into thick slices (4.2oz)
  • Instant brown rice, cooked, 1⅓ cup(s) (9.9oz)
  • Baby spinach, 2 cup(s) (1.3oz)
  • Green onion, 2 medium, finely sliced (1.1oz)
  • Hummus, ½ cup(s) (4.2oz)
  • Parsley, fresh, 2 handful(s), roughly chopped (2.1oz)
  • Lemon, ½ medium, zest and juice (1.5oz)
  • Paprika, ½ tsp(s)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Hummus bliss bowl according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for lunch and store the remaining rice and vegetables in an airtight container in the fridge for lunch later in the week.

Hummus bliss bowl instructions

Preheat the oven to 350°F. Rub the oil over the carrots and peppers. Add only the carrots to a roasting pan and roast in the oven for 20 minutes. Carefully add the red pepper slices to the pan, and cook for a further 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and set aside to cool.

Prepare the rice according to packet instructions.

Into a bowl, add the rice, spinach, roasted vegetables, and green onion. Top with the hummus, parsley, and lemon zest. Squeeze over the lemon juice and sprinkle with a pinch of paprika prior to serving.

recipieName: Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 4 tsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • White onion, chopped, ⅔ cup(s) (3.7oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Thyme, fresh, 2 tsp(s), 5 sprigs (0.1oz)
  • Eggplant, ¼ eggplant(s), unpeeled, chopped (4.8oz)
  • Red bell pepper, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.7oz)
  • Zucchini, 1 medium, diced (6.9oz)
  • Tomatoes, canned, 1 can(s) (6.7oz)
  • Lentils, canned, drained, 1 cup(s), rinsed (6.3oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Portabella mushrooms, 2 piece(s), whole (5.9oz)
  • Arugula, 4 cup(s) (2.8oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner. Store the remaining serving in an airtight container and refrigerate for later in the week.

Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables instructions

Preheat oven 400°F. Lightly grease a medium roasting pan.

Heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil in a medium non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add onion and garlic, cook stirring for 3 minutes until soft. Stir in the thyme, eggplant, bell pepper and zucchini. Cook stirring for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and 1/3 cup of water. Bring to a simmer. Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes until ratatouille thickens slightly. Remove from the heat, stir in the lentils. Season to taste. Spoon into the roasting pan.

Nestle the mushrooms in the ratatouille. Roast for 15 minutes until mushrooms are just tender. Divide into two portions. Spoon remaining 2 teaspoons of oil over the arugula, toss to coat. Scatter the arugula over the mushrooms. Season to taste. Serve.

TIP: If you prefer, you can swap the lentils for 2 poached eggs and serve them on top of the mushrooms and ratatouille.

recipieName: Spicy tuna crispbreads
recipeIngredients:
• Tuna, canned in water, 3 oz(s), drained (3oz)
  • Moroccan seasoning, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Rye crispbread, 4 crispbread(s) (1.4oz)
  • Tomato, ½ medium, whole, chopped (2.2oz)
  • Avocado, 2 tbsp(s), mashed (1.1oz)
  • Carrot, shredded, ¼ cup(s) (1oz)
  • Cucumber, ½ medium, chopped (3.5oz)
  • Red onion, chopped, 1½ tbsp(s) (0.5oz)
  • Red wine vinegar, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
recipeInstructions:
Mix tuna and seasoning in a bowl and spread evenly over crispbreads.

Mix tomato, avocado, carrot, cucumber, onion and vinegar together.

Spread tomato mixture over tuna on crispbreads. Season to taste.

TIP: If you can't find Moroccan seasoning, you can make your own by mixing ground cumin, ground coriander, paprika, ground tumeric and salt.

recipieName: Ginger sesame chicken stir-fry
recipeIngredients:
• Chicken breast, raw, 9 oz(s), sliced (9oz)
  • Ginger, 1 oz(s), about 2-inch piece, shredded (1oz)
  • Tamari, 3 tsp(s), low sodium, divided (0.6oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 2 tbsp(s), divided (1oz)
  • Mushrooms, raw, 1 cup(s), whole, halved (3.4oz)
  • Broccoli, ½ head(s), florets removed, and stem chopped (10.7oz)
  • Baby spinach, 2 cup(s) (1.3oz)
  • Sesame seeds, 2 tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare the Ginger sesame chicken stir-fry according to recipe instructions below.

Reserve half of the stir-fry and half of the sesame seeds in separate airtight containers. Store the stir-fry in the fridge for dinner later in the week.

Ginger sesame chicken stir-fry instructions

Place the chicken, ginger and 1 teaspoon of the tamari in a bowl and season with pepper. Stir to combine.

Heat 2 teaspoons of the oil in a large non-stick wok over a high heat and cook the chicken, stir-frying, for 3 to 4 minutes or until just cooked through. Transfer to a bowl.

Reheat the remaining 4 teaspoons of the oil in the same wok over a high heat. Stir-fry the mushrooms, broccoli and 2 tablespoons of water, for 2 to 3 minutes or until almost tender. Return the chicken to the wok along with the remaining 2 teaspoons of tamari and stir-fry for 30-seconds. Add the baby spinach and toss together until spinach just wilts.

Divide the stir-fry between serving bowls and sprinkle over the sesame seeds.

recipieName: Roasted vegetable pizza
recipeIngredients:
• Red bell pepper, chopped, ⅔ cup(s) (3.5oz)
  • Zucchini, ½ medium, cut into ½ inch pieces (3.5oz)
  • Olive oil spray, 6 x two-second spray(s) (0.4oz)
  • Dried mixed herbs, 3 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Whole-wheat pita, 2 large pita(s) (6-1/2" dia) (4.5oz)
  • Tomato paste, 2 tbsp(s) (1.1oz)
  • Cheddar cheese, reduced-fat, shredded, ⅔ cup(s) (2.6oz)
  • Basil, fresh, 8 leaf(s) (0.1oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es), to taste
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Roast vegetable pizza according to recipe instructions. Serve one pizza for lunch today and transfer remaining pizza to an airtight container and refrigerate for use later in the week.

Roasted vegetable pizza instructions

Preheat oven to 400°F. Arrange vegetables in a small roasting pan. Spray twice with oil then sprinkle over the dried mixed herbs, turn to coat. Roast for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

Spray both sides of each pita with olive oil spray and place on a baking sheet. Spread tomato paste on pitas. Sprinkle each with half the shredded cheese. Top with roasted vegetables then sprinkle with remaining cheese.

Place baking sheet in the oven for 7 minutes until cheese has melted and pita pockets are warm. Sprinkle each with basil leaves. Season and serve.

TIP: The vegetables can be roasted up to 3 days ahead. Keep them in an airtight container in the fridge. If you're taking lunch to work, you can prepare the pizza to end of step 2, wrap in foil and warm in the microwave or in a sandwich press at work. If heating in a sandwich press place the pizza between tw sheets of parchment paper.

recipieName: Cheese & spinach omelet
recipeIngredients:
• Eggs, 2 large (3.5oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Baby spinach, 1 cup(s) (0.7oz)
  • Cheddar cheese, reduced-fat, shredded, 1 tbsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Whole-grain bread, 1 slice(s), toasted (1.1oz)
recipeInstructions:
Crack the eggs into a bowl, season with pepper and whisk. Stir in the baby spinach and cheddar cheese.

Heat the olive oil in a small non-stick skillet over medium heat and swirl to coat.

Pour in the egg mixture. Swirl the pan to evenly coat the base with the eggs. Using a spatula, lift the cooked egg and allow uncooked egg to flow underneath. Cook the egg mixture for about 3 minutes, until partially set. Flip with a spatula and cook for a further 2 to 3 minutes. Reduce heat to low, and continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes, or until done to your liking. 

Once cooked, fold omelet in half and serve with warm toast.

recipieName: Double cheese quesadilla with vegetable sticks & banana
recipeIngredients:
• Cheddar cheese, reduced-fat, shredded, 2½ tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Part-skim ricotta cheese, 3 tbsp(s) (1.6oz)
  • Whole-wheat tortilla, 1 tortilla(s) (1.4oz)
  • Tomato, 1 medium, whole, diced (4.3oz)
  • Lettuce, 1 cup(s), shredded (1.3oz)
  • Avocado, 2 tbsp(s) (1.1oz)
  • Vegetable sticks (carrot, celery, cucumber, bell pepper), 1 cup(s) (4oz)
  • Banana, 1 extra small (2.9oz)
recipeInstructions:
In a small bowl, combine cheddar cheese and ricotta. Spread over one half of the wrap. Top with tomato and fold in half.

Place into a sandwich press, or a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Toast until the cheese has melted and the tortilla is lightly golden.

Serve quesadilla with the lettuce and mashed avocado on top, and vegetable sticks on the side.

DESSERT: Enjoy a banana for dessert.

recipieName: Hoisin pork & vegetable stir-fry
recipeIngredients:
• Quinoa, uncooked, 1⅓ oz(s) (1.3oz)
  • Pork tenderloin, lean, raw, 7 oz(s), cut into strips (7oz)
  • Hoisin sauce, 2 tbsp(s) (1.1oz)
  • Peanut oil, 1 tbsp(s) (0.5oz)
  • Broccoli florets, 2 cup(s) (5oz)
  • Red bell pepper, chopped, 1 cup(s) (5.3oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare the Hoisin pork & vegetable stir-fry according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner.

Store the leftover serving in an airtight container in the fridge for later in the week.

Hoisin pork & vegetable stir-fry instructions

Prepare quinoa according to packet instructions.

In a bowl, combine the pork and half the hoisin sauce. Stir to coat. 

Combine remaining hoisin with 2 tablespoons of water and set aside.

Heat half the oil in a wok or skillet over medium-high heat. Add the pork and cook, while stirring, until just browned, about 2 to 4 minutes. Transfer the pork to a plate and return the wok to the heat.

Heat the remaining oil in the same wok over medium-high heat. Add the broccoli and bell peppers. Place a lid over the wok and steam vegetables, about 2 to 3 minutes. Return the pork to the wok along with the remaining diluted hoisin sauce and the cooked quinoa. Mix to combine and then remove from heat. 

Divide between two serving plates and enjoy.

TIP: Peanut oil is great for high heat stir frying. You can replace with avocado oil for a more neutral flavor or canola oil which is budget friendly.
NutritionInfo: Calories315Total Fat11.1 g- Saturated Fat2.1 gCholesterol65 mgSodium334 mgTotal Carbohydrate27.4 g- Dietary Fiber3.3 g- Total Sugars7.5 g-- Added Sugars0 gProtein26.8 g
